<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Test-Fires Rocket System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 20 (Xinhua) -- India test-fired its multi-barrel
rocket system Wednesday from the interim test range in Orissa
state of eastern India.
</P>
<P>
The rocket system can fire a salvo of 12 rockets in 44 seconds
within a range of 39 km, according to defense sources.
</P>
<P>
The system, capable of carrying different types of warheads,
can destroy solid structures and bunkers. The rocket is aimed at
supplementing the firepower of artillery guns and providing an
edge to the army in low intensity conflicts, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The rocket system has undergone several tests since 1995 and
already reached an advanced stage of experimentation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
