<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 171 HK Citizens Return Home From Indonesia With Help </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 20 (Xinhua) -- A total of 171 Hong Kong citizens
have returned home from Indonesia either through direct
arrangement by or with help from the Chinese Embassy in Indonesia,
according to the Chinese Foreign Ministry Commissioner's Office
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Wu Hongbo, spokesman for the Office of Commissioner of the
Chinese Foreign Ministry in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, said Wednesday that in the past days the Chinese Embassy
in Indonesia has tried its best to provide consular protection and
services to Chinese citizens staying in Indonesia, including Hong
Kong citizens.
</P>
<P>
So far, 486 Chinese citizens have registered at the Chinese
embassy and 310 of them are Hong Kong citizens.
</P>
<P>
An unspecified number of Hong Kong citizens have returned home
by themselves and the embassy is checking the number of the Hong
Kong citizens who are still staying in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
In the past days, the Chinese Embassy in Indonesia has directly
handled 450 telephones for help from the Hong Kong citizens and
240 telephones transmitted by departments concerned of the HKSAR
government.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also expressed his thanks to the Security Bureau
and Immigration Department of the HKSAR for their cooperation with
the office in helping Hong Kong citizens return home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
