<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Hopes for Substantial Dialogue on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian foreign minister
hopes that the meeting between Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic and the Albanians' leader in Kosovo Ibrahim Rugova will
become a really substantial dialogue to anticipate negotiations
between the two parties.
</P>
<P>
While making the announcement at a weekly press conference
Wednesday, Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anda Filip also said that
the foreign minister expresses his satisfaction towards the
American successful diplomatic effort, which made possible the
dialogue and the peaceful settlement of the situation in the
county of Kosovo, by boosting the framework necessary to identify
concrete and long-lasting ways of surmounting the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The minister appreciates the intense activity of the Contact
Group, the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe and
the European Union, as well as the intensive measures of the
states in the area aimed to build up conditions suitable for a
dialogue between the parties and a peaceful climate in Kosovo,
stated Anda Filip.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian Foreign Ministry expresses its readiness to
effectively contribute to the steps aiming at the observance of
ethnic minorities' human rights in Kosovo as well as of the
regional integrity of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
