<HEADLINE> Australia Crash Scotland 5-0 at World Cup Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champions Australia
started soundly at the defence of the women's World Cup title with
a 5-0 win over Scotland in a group A pool match in Utrecht of
Netherlands on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Australians, who had complained about the slippery pitch
before the match, showed a sure touch and footing to dominate the
Scots.
</P>
<P>
They led 2-0 at halftime with goals by Bianca Langham, from a
corner, and a solo effort by Julie Towers.
</P>
<P>
Having missed two fine chances at the start of the second half
they added further goals through Katrina Powell (2) and Alyson
Annan.
</P>
<P>
In the opening group B match England defeated India 1-0.
</P>
<P>
Schoolgirl Lucilla Wright scored the only goal with a well
struck cross shot following a corner in the 19th minute.
</P>
<P>
England failed to convert their territorial advantage into
further goals.
nnnn
</P>
