<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henry Kissinger Becomes Honorary Citizen of His </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Former U.S. Secretary of State Henry
Kissinger has been made an honorary citizen of his German hometown
of Fuerth, a city official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kissinger was born to a schoolteacher's family on May 27, 1923
in the southeastern German city of Fuerth. The Jewish family
emigrated to the United States in 1938 to escape Nazi persecution.
</P>
<P>
Kissinger became a U.S. citizen in 1943 and the national
security adviser of former U.S. President Richard Nixon in 1969.
</P>
<P>
As U.S. secretary of state from 1973 to 1977, he made great
endeavors to promote East-West detente and the establishment of
diplomatic relations between the United States and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
