<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eurofighter Enters Serial Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The Eurofighter combat jet has
entered serial production after 15 years of development and delay,
the German-based company Eurofighter GmbH said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the international air show in Berlin, the company
said that a total of 148 Eurofighter planes are being built in the
first-wave production, with the first deliveries expected to come
by mid-2002.
</P>
<P>
The delta-winged combat jet is a joint creation of Britain,
Germany, Italy and Spain. Under contracts signed earlier this
year, Britain will buy 232 of the new jet, Germany 180, Italy 121
and Spain 87.
</P>
<P>
Company officials disclosed that negotiations were soon to be
held to persuade Norway to become the first foreign buyer with an
order of 30 to 40 planes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
