<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ratings Downgrade for Kwong On Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Fitch IBCA, the international rating
agency, lowered the Long-term rating of Hong Kong's Kwong On Bank
from "A" to "A-" and the Short-term rating from "F1" to "F2."
</P>
<P>
The bank's other ratings, i.e. the Individual rating of "B" and
Support rating of "3," remain unchanged, according to an
announcement by Fitch IBCA here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kwong On Bank is majority owned by Japan's Fuji Bank and the
lowering of its Long-term rating reflects the lowering by Fitch
IBCA of its Long-term rating of Fuji Bank, from "A+" to "A."
</P>
<P>
Fitch IBCA said that Kwong On Bank itself is a sound bank whose
own financial condition is indicated by its Individual rating of
"B."
</P>
<P>
The bank will be affected by the slowdown in Hong Kong's economy
but it is starting from a strong position, and is particularly
well capitalized, the agency added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
