<HEADLINE> India Threatens to Take Pro-Active Manner Against Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Indian Home Minister L. K. Advani
on Wednesday threatened to quell what he called Pakistan's proxy
war in India-held Kashmir and take pro-active manner against
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
In a strongly worded statement here, Advani alleged: "Up to
now, India's policy toward Pakistan's provocations has been
essentially reactive."
</P>
<P>
At the meeting two days back, which was attended by the home
minister, defence minister and chiefs of three-services on Kashmir
issue, "it was decided that further misadventures on Indian
territory shall be dealt with in a pro-active manner," Advani said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan made strong reactions about Advani's threat on
Monday. Reports reaching here Wednesday from Pakistan said that
possibility of an Indian attack on Pakistan-held Kashmir is
increasing following recent threats from New Delhi.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Pakistan armed forces have been put on a maximum
alert. 
</P>
</TEXT>
