<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eurofighter Enters Serial Production Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Berlin, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The Eurofighter combat jet has
entered its production stage after 15 years of development and
repeated delays, the Germany-based company Eurofighter GmbH said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the international air show in Berlin, the company
said a total of 148 Eurofighter planes were to be built in the
first-wave of production, with first deliveries expected to arrive
by the middle of 2002.
</P>
<P>
The delta-winged combat jet is being developed jointly by
Britain, Germany, Italy and Spain. Under contracts signed earlier
this year, Britain will buy 232 of the new jets, Germany 180,
Italy 121 and Spain 87.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations will soon be held to persuade Norway to become the
first foreign buyer with an order for 30 to 40 planes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
