<HEADLINE> Job Ads in Newspapers on Rise in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The number of impermanent jobs
offered in newspaper advertisements in France increased by 41.2
percent in April over the same month last year, Agence
France-Presse quoted the "Manpower" job index as saying Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Manpower" said that the increase shows the rising intention of
French enterprises to employ workers.
</P>
