<HEADLINE> Car Collision Kills 20 in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOGADISHU, May 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 people have died
and more than 40 others were injured when two vehicles collided
Tuesday on the road to Wanleweyn District, 90 km south of
Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Accordung to eyewitnesses, the two vehicles#,a mini-bus
travelling toward Baidoa in the south and a milk transporting
lorry toward Mogadishu had crashed seriously.
</P>
<P>
The serious wounded people had been rushed to the town of
Afgoie and Mogadishu for treatment after the crash, and the
Eyewitnesses had characterized this accident as the worst they
had ever seen in that street which is the best tarmac road in
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the collision is not known. However, the
eyewitnesses attributed it to the lawlessness and high speed in
which both vehicles travelled. "It was obvious that the drivers
had themselves had difficulty in controling their vehicles," said
one of the eyewitnesses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
