<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Suspends All Cross-Border Nuclear Waste </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The German government has ordered the
suspension of all nuclear waste shipments to foreign reprocessing
plants after extremely high radioactive contaminations have been
detected outside many nuclear waste containers.
</P>
<P>
Because of the still undetermined contamination, the nuclear
waste transport to the British reprocessing plant at Sellafield
was also suspended Wednesday after a similar move on May 14
concerning the waste transport to the French La Hague plant, the
German Environment Ministry announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also said that an investigation had been launched
to clarify the issue and proper measures would be taken
afterwards.
</P>
<P>
The Greenpeace and German opposition parties however accused
the Bonn government of having been informed of the contamination
several years ago but having tried to cover up.
</P>
<P>
Rejecting the charge, the Environment Ministry said that it was
informed of the problem by the French side for the first time at
the end of April. Moreover, no contamination had been reported in
Germany so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
