<HEADLINE> French Unions Divided Over Appeal for Strike During </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 20 (Xinhua) -- French trade unions remain divided
over the appeal to stage a strike by truckers during the '98
France World Cup Football finals.
</P>
<P>
The Force Ouvriere (FO) has called for a blockade of France's
roads from late May to June to push the employers to raise the
salaries of truckers.
</P>
<P>
While reserving the right to give an order of strike, the
Confederation Generale du Travaile (CGT) Wednesday also called on
the truckers to "take the initiatives for defending their
requests" on salary raise.
</P>
<P>
However, the federation of transports and tourism CFE-CGC
denounced the FO appeal for strike, describing the act as
"opportunistic." 
</P>
