<HEADLINE> Annan Names New Special Representative for Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 20 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan announced Wednesday that he has appointed Jan Kubis to
replace Gerd Merrem as his special representative for Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
Merrem relinquishes his post on May 30 and will retire after 25
years of service in the U.N. and a two year posting in Tajikistan,
according to a U.N. press release.
</P>
<P>
Kubis, 46, is a Slovak citizen and has held the position of the
director of the Conflict Prevention Center in the Secretariat of
the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe since
1994. 
