<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-20 20:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cypriot President Reassures Aid to Economic Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot President Glafcos Clerides
Wednesday said his government will go all out to make the economy
very competitive.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the 23rd Cyprus
International Fair, Clerides said that the government will prepare
reform plans for each economic sector later this year.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 exhibitors representing 1,600 companies from 40
countries took part in the annual fair.
</P>
<P>
"Today, on the threshold of the 21st century, the Cyprus
economy has to go through a difficult course," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Cypriot president called for people's support to his
government in facing the challenges brought about by the
globalization of the world economy.
</P>
<P>
He said the government's basic strategy is to create a strong
economy to survive competition in European Union's large market
and help Cyprus become the regional trade and business hub.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus entered accession talks with the European Union last
March.
</P>
<P>
The ways to achieve the goals are to reform fiscal systems,
strengthen productive sectors, encourage economic modernization
and restructuring and conform to gradual liberalization of
markets, Clerides said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
