<HEADLINE> U.N. Council Calls for End to Violence in Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Security
Council issued a presidential statement on Wednesday calling for
an immediate end to violence against civilians in Sierra Leone,
a West African country.
</P>
<P>
Expressing grave concern about reported foreign military support
to the country's rebels, the Council called on all states to
strictly observe the relevant U.N. resolution and avoid
destabilizing the situation in that country.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the efforts by the democratically-elected government
since its return on March 10 1998, the Council urged all rebels to
cease resistance, lay down their arms and surrender to forces
of the Military Observer Group (ECOMOG) of the Economic Community
of West African States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
