<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0059 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Han Xue Wins Women's 50m Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAODING, North China, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Han Xue, a world top
women's short-course breaststroker, stunned favorite Hu Xiaowen to
capture the women's 50 meters freestyle on the last day of the
Chinese national swimming championships here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old clocked 25.67 seconds for the win, beating Hu
to second by seven hundredths of a second. Nian Yun finished third
in 25.92.
</P>
<P>
Han, world record holder in the short-course 50m breaststroke,
never thought she could win the title of freestyle.
</P>
<P>
"I had never expected to take the sprint freestyle crown," she
said. "My personal best, set in the national trials for the 1996
Olympic Games, was just 25.97 seconds."
</P>
<P>
The Beijing native added: "I could feel someone was keeping
shoulder with me untill the last five meters. I held my breath and
tried my best to touch the pad. I didn't know I was the winner
till I saw the time on the scoreboard."
</P>
<P>
Hu, world record holder of the short-course 100m individual
medley, attributed her loss to the lack of experience. "I was
less experienced in the finishing techniques than Han," she
said. "Anyway, this is my debut in this sprint event."
</P>
<P>
Chen Yan from Liaoning Province, double world champion and
world record holder of the 400m individual medley, took the silver
in the 200m backstroke in 2:16.53, behind her namesake Chen Yan
from Jiangsu Province in 2:14.27.
</P>
<P>
The seven-day championships, which introduced semi-finals for
the first time, has attracted 280 swimmers from 29 clubs across
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
