<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Affects Life in Southern Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Searing heat has been making life
difficult in the Terai plain of southern Nepal in the past few
days, the official RSS news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In Janakpurdham, the blistering sun has driven rickshaws, the
main means of transport in the town, off the streets, shops remain
closed, and school attendance is low, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Heat has brought people with typhoid and diarrhea thronging to
hospital, it said, adding that irregularity in power supply has
compounded the problem.
</P>
<P>
In Saptari district, day time temperature exceeds 40 degrees
centigrade, and children who suffer from dysentery and diarrhea
with vomiting are flocking to hospital.
</P>
<P>
Vegetables are drying up while leaf and stalk diseases have
overtaken the summer paddy, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Day time temperature in Mahendranagar is as high as 40 to 42
degrees centigrade. Schools have to have classes in the morning.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile flies and mosquitoes are proliferating in the area,
the news agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
