-- A satellite failure disrupted communications across the
United States. Most pager customers were affected, as well as some
radio and TV broadcasts, airline flights, retail
telecommunications and self-service gasoline pumps. PanAmSat, 81
percent owned by GM's Hughes unit, may require several days to
restore service. 
