<HEADLINE> Wind Rekindles Inner Mongolian Forest Fire Embers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A strong wind has fanned the embers
of the forest fire in north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region into raging flames again.
</P>
<P>
This was reported by the local firefighting headquarters in the
Greater Xin'gan Mountain Range.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which was brought under control yesterday, sprang up
again along a four-to-five-km stretch of the southeast front this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The fire on the northeast front is almost under control,
according to the headquarters.
</P>
<P>
As many as 350 forest rangers have been assembled at the
firefighting front, and the whole area is under close
monitoring. In addition, two helicopters equipped with water tanks
have been summoned, and preparations for making artificial
rainfall are under way. 
</P>
