<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Government Adopts Measures to Relax Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Russian cabinet in a meeting
Thursday adopted a package of measures designed to ease the
current crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko said the measures were aimed at
increasing revenue and cutting government expenditures.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will not impose additional taxes but
promised to regulate the taxation system.
</P>
<P>
If the owners of enterprises fail to pay their debts, all their
assets would be confiscated, he said.
</P>
<P>
In order to bring in more revenue, the government decided to
set up or increase taxes on those products, particularly food
products, that can be manufactured in Russia.
</P>
<P>
However, the import tax for advanced technologies and equipment
will be reduced.
</P>
<P>
The government will also levy higher taxes on those enterprises
that are unable to use land efficiently or those that have already
gone bankrupt.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Russia will also strengthen control over the alcohol
market.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko pointed out that the government has decided to cut 43
overseas business offices in an effort to reduce expenditures.
</P>
<P>
On the current financial situation in Russia, the prime
minister said the government brought the situation under control
when the Central Bank raised interest rates following the crisis
that hit the security market last Friday.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the financial crisis mainly to the country's
heavy debts but made it clear that Russia will pay all its
internal and external debts.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko said that despite a complicated market situation,
there can be no talk about the government's failure to fulfill its
commitments.
</P>
<P>
At the session, the premier stressed the need for sticking to a
firm budget. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
