<HEADLINE> Hong Kong To Set Off "Olympic Day Run" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Over 1,500 recreation and serious
runners are expected to gather at the Shing Mun River Channel
venue for Hong Kong's annual "Olympic Day Run" in Shatin on June
21, organizers announced here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 event is organized by the Hong Kong Amateur Athletic
Association under the patronage of the International Olympic
Committee (IOC) and the Amateur Sports Federation and Olympic
Committee of Hong Kong, China (ASF&AMP;OC).
</P>
<P>
The organizers had given this year's Run a theme "Sports and
Health" to reinforce community awareness of the benefits of
exercise to general health.
</P>
<P>
"The Olympic Ideals is about taking part and it is the mission
of the ASF&AMP;OC to spread that spirit within Hong Kong. The Olympic
Day Run is an annual global effort of the IOC to spread the
Olympic Ideals in every country," said Timothy Fok, president of
the ASF&AMP;OC.
</P>
<P>
The participants of the Olympic Day Run will begin with a lap
around the track of the Hong Kong Sports Institute and then the
group will run on to the cycle path along the Channel, with a
total length of about six kilometers. 
</P>
