<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Its Largest Christianity Research Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A research center on Christianity
was set up here today under the Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences.
</P>
<P>
According to Dr. Zhuo Xinping, the center's first director, the
center is the largest of its kind in China and will play a
leading role in China's Christianity research.
</P>
<P>
He said that currently there are over 10 research institutes on
Christianity in China, involving nearly 200 full-time
researchers. During the past five years, some 50 books in this
field have been published in China.
</P>
<P>
The expert said that China's Christianity research has
made significant progress since the reform and opening-up started
in late 1978.
</P>
<P>
"Now Chinese scholars participate in most of the international
workshops held on Christianity, and books written by Chinese
Christianity researchers have drawn attention from academic
circles all over the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Liu Ji, vice-president of the Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences, addressed today's inaugural meeting, saying that
research on Christianity -- including Catholicism, the Orthodox
Eastern Church and Protestantism -- is very important for getting
to know both the world and mankind better.
</P>
<P>
He said that although the history of China's research in this
regard is not long, full importance has been paid by the related
departments from the very beginning.
</P>
<P>
He said the new center will promote China's Christianity
research and act as an open window on China's religious policy for
foreigners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
