<HEADLINE> Top Australian Weightlifter Banned for Positive Drug Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Australian Harvey Goodman was
banned for two years on Thursday after the weightlifting champion
was found for an illegal testosterone level.
</P>
<P>
An independent tribunal found the triple Commonwealth champion
had breached anti-drug guidelines. The Australian Weightlifting
Federation (AWF) confirmed the finding and said it would enforce
the ban.
</P>
<P>
Goodman tested positive in a drug test carried out in June
18. AWF executive director Robert Kabbas said Goodman had argued
that he had taken a ginseng-based herbal remedy.
</P>
<P>
When competitors record an above normal testosterone level it
can indicate they have ingested testosterone or steroids.
</P>
</TEXT>
