<BODY>
<HEADLINE> River Plate Edges Colon in Libertadores Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The under-strength River
Plate scored a 2-1 win over fellow Argentines Colon in the first
leg of their South American Libertadores Cup quarter-final in
Buenos Aires on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Five-times champions Penarol from Uruguay enjoyed a 2-0 home
win against Paraguay's Cerro Porteno in the day's other game.
</P>
<P>
River Plate were missing five players involved in Argentina's
World Cup preparations, two with Paraguay and leading striker
Marcelo Salas with Chile.
</P>
<P>
But they were still too strong for Colon. All the goals came in
the first half with Colombia's Juan Pablo Angel scoring the winner
a minute before halftime.
</P>
<P>
A last-minute strike by veteran Uruguayan international Pablo
Bengoechea gave Penarol a two-goal lead after Jose Franco had put
the Uruguayan champions ahead in the 20th minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
