<HEADLINE> Yates to Return to International Circuit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Former Tour de France star Sean
Yates will return to international cycling in the Prutour of
Britain starting on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 38-year-old, one of only three Britons to have worn the
yellow jersey on the Tour de France, will replace the
injury-plagued Scot Gamble in the Linda McCartney Foods team.
</P>
<P>
Although Yates retired from the international circuit two years
ago, he has continued to race in Britain and is the current
national 50-mile time trial champion. 
</P>
