<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Australia Win Openers in Men's Hockey Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Pakistan and
Australia both won their openers when the men's event got underway
on the second day of the ninth World Field Hockey Championships in
Utrecht, the Netherlands, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan trounced Asian rivals Malaysia with a 7-2 victory
while Australia achieved their biggest ever win over Poland with
an 8-0 success.
</P>
<P>
But former champions India suffered a disastrous 4-1 defeat to
1992 Olympic champions Germany, with four goals conceded in the
first half.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's goals were shared between seven different players,
Shahbaz Ahmed senior scoring the best of the match, a solo effort
for Pakistan's third in the 27th minute. 
</P>
