<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC, CPPCC Officials Inspect Supreme People's Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Xiao Yang, president of China's
Supreme People's Court, stressed here today that a sound public
supervision system, especially supervision by the legislature and
advisory body, is an important guarantee of the impartiality of
the people's court.
</P>
<P>
Invited by the Supreme People's Court, some members of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) as well
as some members and Standing Committee members of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) inspected it and gave instructions on its work,
yesterday and today, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The move is regarded as one of the practical measures that the
Supreme People's Court has taken to rectify itself by directly
soliciting criticism and suggestions from the NPC and the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
Xiao said that it is the starting point for the work of the
people's court to practice the rule of law and ensure judicial
justice. Greater efforts must be made to improve the
quality of the judges and eliminate corruption in the judicial
sector.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the instructions of the central government as
well as the criticism and suggestions from NPC and CPPCC
members, the people's court will work hard to stop abuses of
power by judges.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the court will rectify disciplinary procedures and
solve such problems as judges and court staff leaking secrets and
accepting bribes, Xiao said.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
