<HEADLINE> New Domestic Aircraft to Be on Display in Zhuhai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Aviation Industries of China (AVIC)
will choose 18 new-generation transport or fighter aircraft,
including the FBC-1, Zhi-9G, Zhi-11, Yun-7-200 and K8, to attend
the '98 Air Show in the south China city of Zhuhai in November.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first public exhibition for a batch of
China-made aircraft. The planes will also conduct flight
performances, said Liu Gaozhuo, vice-president of AVIC.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that more advanced air products and aviation
technology will be exhibited at the '98 Air Show, compared with
the previous one, held in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Boeing, Airbus, Rolls-Royce, BMW and Benz have promised to
increase the number of their exhibits at the show. Canada, Italy
and Russia, among other countries, will send large delegations to
the show.
</P>
<P>
The event will feature commercial flight demonstrations, as
well as performances by precision military flight teams from
China, Russia, the United States, and France.
</P>
<P>
The '98 Air Show will be jointly sponsored by the Civil
Aviation Administration of China, AVIC, China Aerospace Corp. and
the Zhuhai city government, with Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo as
chairman of the organizing committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
