<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Torrential Rain Leaves 8 Missing in Gansu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were reported missing
and four were injured when torrential rain lashed parts of Gansu
Province in northwest China on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In Yongdeng, a suburban county of this capital of Gansu, heavy
rain washed away 80 houses, destroyed reservoirs, river dykes and
highways, and flooded 333 ha of crops.
</P>
<P>
In Gaolan County more than 600 buildings collapsed and over
2,600 ha of farmland was inundated. The flooding also disrupted
electricity supplies, causing blackouts in many townships.
</P>
<P>
According to the local meteorological station, the rainfall
reached 74 mm in some places. Government officials and local
people are exerting joint efforts to cleaning up the aftermath of
the downpour.  
</P>
</TEXT>
