<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Volatile Trade at Karachi Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE)
saw a volatile session Thursday rising dramatically in the morning
session but closing the day relatively unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 Index Thursday gained 1.26 points to close at
1,250.86 points against Wednesday's closing of 1,249.60.
</P>
<P>
A total of 81 million shares were traded Thursday against 121
million shares traded the previous day. There were 51 gainers and
47 losers.
</P>
<P>
Having hit a five-year low in trade Wednesday, analysts
remained wary of a rebound at the KSE-100 Index.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the confidence of the investors will likely
remain weak until Pakistan's dispute with India on the latter's
nuclear tests and the issues relating to the independent power
producers are resolved.
</P>
<P>
Analysts expect trade on Friday to be dull and the KSE-100
Index is likely to show little change. 
</P>
</TEXT>
