<HEADLINE> China's B-Share Market Expected to Bottom Out (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Besides, only a limited number of enterprises can be listed on
overseas capital markets, and not all Chinese enterprises can meet
the qualifications for listing overseas.
</P>
<P>
"Investors should not feel depressed about the B-share market,"
said Coull. "All markets in the world go through this, and the
B-share market is no exception.
</P>
<P>
"I'm quite confident that prices of B-shares will represent
value for someone, and investors will come back to the market."
</P>
<P>
Coull's view was echoed by stock analysts with the Jun'an
Securities Co. Ltd, who said that the current B-share market
provides the best investment opportunities. They said that they
expected the Shenzhen B-share index to gain 67 percent at the most
in the near future, and Shanghai, 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say the authorities are expected to take measures to
improve the investment climate of the sluggish B-share market and
to enliven the trading for the rest of this year. Various upcoming
policy incentives will trigger a strong upward trend on the
B-share market, they added. 
</P>
