<HEADLINE> France Calls on Indonesia to Carry Out Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- France said on Thursday that the
resignation of President Suharto should lead to the implementation
of "indispensable political and economic reforms" in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The French Foreign Ministry said that France expects Indonesia
to return to political stability and resume programs of economic
readjustment.
</P>
<P>
"France will continue to bring its support to the Indonesian
people all along this process," said the foreign ministry in a
communique. 
</P>
