<HEADLINE> Taiwan Delegation Offers Opinions On Draft Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A Taiwan delegation comprising
people from political circles, businessmen, law experts and
scholars visited this Chinese capital from May 17 through 21.
</P>
<P>
The visit was sponsored by the Beijing-based Association for
Relations Across the Taiwan Straits (ARAYS) to solicit opinions
from Taiwan people about a draft law on protecting Taiwan
investment in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen met with the people from political
circles in the delegation on Tuesday, and expressed his
appreciation for what they had done to protect the legal rights of
Taiwan business people.
</P>
<P>
The delegation exchanged views with mainland officials from the
Supreme People's Court, the State Development Planning Commission,
State Economic and Trade Commission, Ministry of Public Security,
Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation and Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The members of the delegation said that it is wise for the
mainland to work on a law to protect Taiwan investors and to
listen to opinions from Taiwan people. The move shows the respect
for public opinion, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
