<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's "Olympic Day Run" to Promote Sports, Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Over 1,500 recreation and serious
runners are expected to gather at the Shing Mun River Channel venue
for Hong Kong's annual "Olympic Day Run" in Shatin, the New
Territories, on June 21 this year, organizers announced here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 event is organized by the Hong Kong Amateur Athletic
Association under the patronage of the International Olympic Committee
and the Amateur Sports Federation and Olympic Committee of Hong Kong,
China (ASF&AMP;OC), with sponsorship by Hang Seng Bank, Provisional Urban
Council and Provisional Regional Council and Swire Coca-Cola HK Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The organizers had given this year's Run a theme "Sports and
Health" to reinforce community awareness of the benefits of exercise
to general health.
</P>
<P>
"The Olympic Ideals is about taking part and it is the mission of
the ASF&AMP;OC to spread that spirit within Hong Kong. The Olympic Day
Run is an annual global effort of the IOC to spread the Olympic Ideals
in every country," said Timothy Fok, President of the ASF&AMP;OC.
</P>
<P>
The participants of the Olymic Day Run will begin with a lap around
the track of the Hong Kong Sports Institute and then the group will
run ontothe cycle path along the Channel, with a total length of about
six kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
