<HEADLINE> Fireworks Factory Blast Toll Rises to Nine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- An explosion at a fireworks
factory in south China's Guangdong Province on May 19 killed nine
people and injured 46. Two people, including a Japanese technician,
are reported missing.
</P>
<P>
The blast took place in a Sino-Japanese joint venture in Bolou
County, when a Japanese technician and two Chinese workers were
testing a new firework model.
</P>
<P>
The subsequent blaze last about one hour and a half, and totally
destroyed the factory building.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 policemen and fire fighters took part in the
rescue operation, joined by over 100 doctors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
