<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Calls for Better Performance from State Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji said here
yesterday that the diversion of redundant workers to other jobs
and reemployment of laid-off workers are active measures for the
reform of state-owned enterprises and must be done well.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks while visiting the Beijing No.1 Machine
Tool Factory with officials from the State Council and Beijing
Municipal Government.
</P>
<P>
Following a workshop tour, a seminar was held at the
factory with the participation of officials in charge of
state enterprises and some laid-off workers, who talked about their
experiences in earning their own livings.
</P>
<P>
After hearing a work report from Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin, the
premier said that the current economic situation in Beijing is
good, and that the city will contribute more to the national
economy.
</P>
<P>
He urged municipal officials to work out countermeasures to
solve the problem of low efficiency and losses in some
industrial enterprises, noting that the diversion of redundant
workers to other jobs is an active and feasible move to revitalize
state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Laid-off workers should be encouraged to go in for service
trades, and there is great potential in this regard in Beijing,
Zhu said, adding that the government will keep on improving
the social security system to relieve the worries of laid-off
workers.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, he called on Beijing officials to do a
good job of reforming the current grain circulation system and to
boost comprehensive development of the capital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
