<HEADLINE> Karpov to Open Lebanese Chess Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 21 (Xinhua) -- World chess champion Anatoly Karpov
will open Lebanon's first international chess tournament,
organizers said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Karpov, five-time world champion, will play two exhibition
matches where he will be pitted against 30 players at once,
Lebanese chess federation president Ammar Houry said.
</P>
<P>
Players from 16 countries, mainly Arab and European, will take
part in the tournament next Wednesday. 
