<HEADLINE> Canada Opens Consulate in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Canada today set up a consulate in
southwest China's Chongqing City, the country's fourth
municipality directly under the central government.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Canadian Industry Minister John Manley and Communist
Party Secretary of Chongqing Zhang Delin attended today's
inauguration ceremony for the consulate, Canada's fourth in China.
</P>
<P>
Manley said the establishment of the consulate is aimed at
strengthening economic cooperation between Canada and the western
part of China, and at exploring local markets for Canadian
companies.
</P>
<P>
Manley said his country has always value Chongqing's
development potential, and is ready to help it become an
international metropolis.
</P>
<P>
Manley is in China with a group of Canadian company managers
involved in telecommunications, transportation and the power
industry.
</P>
<P>
Also today, the two sides signed two agreements on economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Canada set up its first embassy in Chongqing in 1942. 
</P>
</TEXT>
