<HEADLINE> Top Legislator Meets Anna Chennault </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of China's
National People's Congress Standing Committee, met here today with
American social activists Anna Chan Chennault and Irving Kaufman.
</P>
<P>
Chan, an American of Chinese origin, briefed Li on her talks
with China's Education Ministry on setting up an Anna Chan
Chennault education award to honor primary and secondary school
teachers.
</P>
<P>
Li reiterated China's strategy of reinvigorating the nation
through developing science and education.
</P>
<P>
On the necessity of promoting education in ethnic-minority
areas and poor areas, Li stressed that education is needed to
train personnel, improve the people's cultural quality, develop
ethnic-minority areas and help poor areas achieve prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Li thanked the two activists for their concern and support for
China's education for many years.
</P>
<P>
The visitors, who are here as guests of the Education Ministry,
will also visit the cities of Taiyuan and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
