<HEADLINE> Angola Calls for Foreign Investment in Natural </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Angola has called for foreign
investment in the field of natural gas to boost relevant
industries in petro-chemical, agricultural, fertilizer and energy
sectors.
</P>
<P>
The call was made by Minister of Petroleum Albina Assis at the
just concluded southern African Economic Summit in Windhoek,
Namibia.
</P>
<P>
Assis told the press on returning here Wednesday night from
Windhoek that she has briefed the summit on the prospects of
Angola's petroleum industry.
</P>
<P>
Oil industry is the country's pillar industry, with a daily
production of 750,000 barrels.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, up to now, 50 companies are now
engaged in oil tapping and production in the southern African
country, including two world-renowned companies.
</P>
<P>
She said the theme of the summit was to promote investment in
southern Africa and that the U.S. Coke Cola Company is now
negotiating with Angola on setting up a plant in Bengo province
near Luanda to produce soft drinks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
