<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Concerned About Its Citizens in Indonesia: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China is paying close attention to
the development of the situation in Indonesia and is concerned
about Chinese citizens in that Southeast Asian country, Chinese
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
Responding to a reporter's question, Zhu said that, upon
instructions from home, the Chinese Embassy in Indonesia is
sparing no efforts to provide consular protection and assistance
to Chinese citizens in Indonesia, including compatriots from Hong
Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The embassy has registered Chinese citizens there and kept
close contact with them. It has also transferred some
Indonesian-Chinese to safe areas, he noted.
</P>
<P>
For those Indonesian-Chinese who want to leave Indonesia, the
embassy has worked hard to give them all necessary help and
facilities, and arranged with the Cathay Pacific Airways and
Southern China Airlines to put on more flights to and from
Indonesia, Zhu said, adding that relevant departments in China are
also working hard for this.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to pay close attention to the development
of the situation in Indonesia as well as the situation of the
Indonesian-Chinese in that country, and take proper measures to
provide them and Chinese citizens with all necessary assistance,
Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
With regard to Indonesian-Chinese, Zhu said that many of them
have relatives in China, and their relatives are also concerned
about their plight.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, China hopes the situation in Indonesia will calm
down as soon as possible, and that the Indonesian Government will
take effective measures to protect the lives and properties of all
ethnic groups in the country, including the Indonesian-Chinese, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
