<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Air Force Saves Life of Japanese Tourist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese air force saved the
life of a Japanese visitor to the Ganzi Plateau in southwest
China's Sichuan Province Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The 77-year-old tourist suffered from pneumonedema, caused by
mountain hypoxia. He was immediately taken to the nearest county
hospital.
</P>
<P>
But the serious condition of the patient required his immediate
transfer to a larger hospital. After receiving an emergency
message from the county hospital, the emergency center in this
provincial capital asked the air force to bring the patient
by helicopter.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter accomplished its mission in two hours, flying as
high as 6,000 m in complicated weather conditions.
</P>
<P>
The man is now in stable condition in a hospital here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
