<HEADLINE> China's Steel, Iron Output Continues To Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China produced 27.31 million tons
of pig iron during the first quarter, 6.9 percent more than in the
same 1997 period, announced the State Statistics Bureau today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, steel output reached 26.77 million tons, up 5.9
percent from the figure for the same 1997 period. Output of
rolled steel was 23.28 million tons, up 6.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, Northeast China's Liaoning Province and North China's
Hebei Province were the top three iron and steel producers, with
their output reaching 3.8 million tons, 3.31 million tons and 2.56
million tons, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
