<HEADLINE> Hang Seng China Enterprises Index Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng China Enterprises Index
fell 4.94 points to close at 589.88 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Index, introduced in August 1995, tracks the overall
performance of 40 China's state-owned enterprises listed on the
Hong Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index rose 12.31 points from the previous
session to close at 914.65.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index comprises 50 stocks ranked from 101
to 150 on the Hong Kong bourse in terms of market capitalization
and turnover.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index dropped 21.78
points to close at 1,299.20.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index tracks the
performance of 32 locally-listed companies with a significant
equity interest held by entities in China.
</P>
<P>
The three segmented Hang Seng indices are devised by Hang Seng
Index (HSI) Services Limited, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Hang
Seng Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
