<HEADLINE> HK Lucky Shoppers to Take Off at New Airport on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's largest supermarket
chain, Wellcome, has chartered a flight to carry some 250 lucky
customers to Manila on July 6, the first day the new airport goes
into operation.
</P>
<P>
Customers, who purchase 100 HK dollars or more worth of goods
at Wellcome during the four-week promotion period, will have the
chance to join a lucky draw to win three-day holidays in Manila,
the Philippines, the supermarket chain announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Lewis McMullen, Wellcome's marketing manager, told a press
briefing Thursday: "It is a historical flight on a memorable day."
He said that the promotion would give customers an opportunity to
take part in one of Hong Kong's most important events by taking
off from the new airport on its opening day.
</P>
<P>
Built on Chek Lap Kok, a tiny island in the west of the Hong
Kong Island, the new airport is claimed to be the largest
infrastructure project in Hong Kong's history. It is scheduled to
be opened on July 6, 1998 after seven years of construction.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1945, Wellcome has extended its chain to every
corner of Hong Kong. About 13 million customers frequent its 220
stores across the city every month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
