<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher as Suharto Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks jumped higher on
Thursday as the resignation of Indonesian President Suharto
boosted the market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
The 33-stock Hang Seng Index rallied 121.27 points, or 1.27
percent, to close at 9,670.45, following a 37-point gain and a
100-point gain for Tuesday and Wednesday respectively.
</P>
<P>
Buyers returned to the market with their nerves calmed by
the news of the peaceful transition of power in Indonesia, brokers
said.
</P>
<P>
Stronger markets elsewhere in the region and easing local
interest rates also helped boost investors' confidence, they said.
</P>
<P>
Finance and properties sectors led the increase, up 2.49
percent and 1.82 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Trading volume totaled 7,208 million HK dollars (924 million
U.S. dollars), slightly down compared with Wednesday. The index
heavyweight HSBC Holdings dominated the market, accounting for
nearly a quarter of total turnover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
