<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Less Companies Established in Macao in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department on Thursday show that the number of newly-established
firms increased 11.2 percent from last quarter.
</P>
<P>
Most of the new companies deal with such business as wholesale
and retailing, repair of automobiles, motorcycles and family
appliances, hotels and restaurants. Other business includes
finance and property dealings.
</P>
<P>
In addition, about 87 percent of the new companies are small
ones with registered capital of less than 100,000 patacas (about
12,500 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a total of 17 companies wound up their business in
the first quarter, involving some 5.80 million patacas (about
725,000 U.S. dollars) of registered capital. They were mostly
manufacturing factories.  
</P>
</TEXT>
