<HEADLINE> Primary School Teachers Study Macao Basic Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 21 (Xinhua) -- About 100 teachers from all sorts of
primary schools in Macao gathered together on Thursday to study
the basic law of Macao in a part-time course.
</P>
<P>
This is the latest event in the growing trend to learn the
basic law among Macao residents. Macao grassroots organizations,
civil service groups and even the Macao-born Portuguese
communities have started their own course to make themselves
familiar with the law.
</P>
<P>
Lau Sin Peng, director of the Macao Chinese Education
Association, which organized the course, told Xinhua that her
association had to expand the class from one to two now as it was
overwhelmed with applications from local primary schools,
including those private- and publicly-funded.
</P>
<P>
"It is today's students who will abide by, implement and
defend the basic law of Macao in the future," she said. "But to
make the students familiar with the law we must first let the
teachers know the law, that's why we start the course."
</P>
<P>
She said that encouraged by the teachers' enthusiasm to the
course, her association plans to hold more in the future,
including one set for the summer vacation.
</P>
<P>
Following the publication of the Macao Basic Law Textbook in
1994, more and more primary and middle schools in Macao have
initiated the basic law course. 
</P>
</TEXT>
