<HEADLINE> France to Host Brazilian Cultural Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- France will host a Brazilian cultural
 exhibition sponsored by the Brazilian government in Louvre Museum
in Paris during the 1998 France Football World Cup finals,
reported Agence France-Presse on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Carrousel of Louvre, which is under the central square of
the Louvre Palace, will display from June 15 to 28 a model of
Amazonian forestry on 900 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Images of rivers, people, plants and flowers of the Amazonian
forests, the world's biggest tropical forest group, will be
transmitted by satellites, while the replica of an Indian village
will be on display.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the Amazonian forests, the exhibition will also
display sceneries and panoramas of other parts of Brazil, the
country's Baroque arts, and industrial products from 50 Brazilian
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
A Brazilian movie week will be held in the Chaillot National
Theater while a four-day international seminar on Brazil's
economic and social issues will be sponsored by the Brazilian
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
