<HEADLINE> Zambia's Flower Exports Increase by 35 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's flower exports to the
European market stood at 5,231 tons last year compared to 3,861
tons in 1996, with a 35 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Steven Humphreys, Chief Executive of the Export Board of
Zambia said Wednesday that the Zambia Export Growers Association
will continue providing quality services to its members in 1998
to achieve a 30 percent growth in flower exports this year over
last year, Times of Zambia reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Rose flowers registered 45 percent of the total exports, said
Humphreys.
</P>
<P>
Flower growers in Zambia have put 500 hectares under flower
production this year to achieve sharp increases in flower
exports.
</P>
<P>
The association has embarked on a training program for farm
supervisors to impart on them modern flower management skills to
ensure that the produce meet the international standards.
</P>
<P>
In Zambia, the management of horticultural exports is still
dependent on foreign expertise because of a shortage of qualified
local personnel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
