<HEADLINE> 1 Hezbollah Militant Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 21 (Xinhua) -- One militant of Lebanon's
pro-Iranian Hezbollah was killed overnight in south Lebanon during
an Israeli attack, the Voice of the People radio reported here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The militant was killed when shells fired by Israeli troops
crashed in the village of Soujud in the eastern sector of the
occupied zone, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli army has confirmed the fatality, saying in a
communique that at least one "terrorist" was killed in its latest
attack on a guerrilla unit in the occupied zone.
</P>
<P>
There is no report of Israeli casualties so far.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, or Party of God, is leading a guerrilla war to fight
about 2,000 Israeli occupation forces and their 2,500-strong
allied militiamen.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its northern
areas from Lebanese guerrilla cross-border attacks. 
