<P>
National Australia Bank fell 7.3 cents to 22.09 Australian
dollars and the Commonwealth Bank of Australia dropped 14.7 cents
to 18.903 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index rose 7.1 points to 1121.1.
</P>
<P>
Australia's leading company BHP rose 13 cents to 13.66
Australian dollars while global miner Rio Tinto improved 15 cents
to 20.20 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index dropped 19.4 points to 1241.8 as the bullion
price improved 1.70 U.S. dollars to 299.50 U.S. dollars per ounce.
</P>
<P>
National turnover Thursday was 371 million shares at a value of
818.35 million U.S. dollars, with falls of 537 bettering rises of
518. 
</P>
