Tojo, hanged in 1948 for crimes against humanity, came out last
Saturday in 140 movie halls. It depicted the Japanese army invading
Asian countries as a ``liberation army'' freeing Asia from white
colonialism. The film also paid hommage to Indian judge Radhabinod
Pal, the only one of 11 judges at the Tokyo Far-East Military
Tribunal who pleaded for acquitting Tojo.
