his attitude toward the president of the republic and called for
a ``most total reservation'' by the members of his cabinet in
making comment on judicial issues. Jospin said that he and
President Chirac have never engaged in any kind of battle against
each other, although they hold different convictions.
</P>
<P>
-- With the theme of ``the Oceans, a Patrimony for the Future,''
an exhibition will be opened on Thursday in the Portuguese capital
Lisbon in the presence of 12 chiefs of state and government. The
exhibition is presented as a window of modern Portugal and will
recall a golden age of ocean sailings. It also falls on the 500th
anniversary of the arrival in the Western Indian islands by Vasco de
Gama on May 21, 1498. 
