<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin on China's Unofficial Diplomacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China's non-governmental diplomatic
work is mainly aimed to build up mutual understanding, trust and
friendship among the people around the world, President Jiang
Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with members of the Seventh Council of the
Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries
(CPAFFC) at the Great Hall of the People, Jiang said the CPAFFC, a
major organization engaged in unofficial diplomacy, has played a
vital role in improving China's international environment and for
the country's domestic construction over the past four decades.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the hope that China's non-governmental diplomatic
work will continue promoting international economic and cultural
cooperation through existing unofficial channels to the service of
China's reform, opening-up and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called on the CPAFFC to continue to involve itself in
forging sisterly-city ties with other countries so as to
facilitate the Chinese cities' international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji and Vice-Premier Qian Qichen were along with
President Jiang at the meeting with over 280 CPAFFC Council
members, who are attending its seventh council meeting that opened
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The CPAFFC, founded in 1954, has so far set up cooperative
relationships with 364 unofficial organizations in 115
countries. Moreover, it has helped form 821 pairs of sisterly-city
relationships between the Chinese cities or provinces with their
counterparts in other countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
