<HEADLINE> Beijing's "Electronic Street" Eyeing on High Targets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Enterprises in Zhongguancun, known
as a "Silicon Valley", in the Haidian District of the Chinese
capital, are working hard for higher development targets.
</P>
<P>
They expect to generate a combined income of 70 billion yuan
(8.2 billion U.S. dollars) by the year 2000 through upgrading the
industries and expand the market.
</P>
<P>
Zhongguancun, popularly known as an "electronic street", is
home to over 2,700 high-tech enterprises engaging in research,
development, production and selling of computers and information
technological products, including China's top computer companies,
the Legend Computer Group Co. and the Beijing Stone Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The street has become China's largest trading center for
computers and related products after ten years of development.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the street's total income stood at over 34 billion
yuan (4.09 billion US dollars), 25 fold the figure a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment in the area has also been on the rise, with
the figure for 1997 reaching 1.29 million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
