<HEADLINE> China Transfers Resource Renewable Technology to Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China has for the first time sold
its technology on the utilization of reclaimed resources to
foreign companies, it is learned here today.
</P>
<P>
The Rebound Rubber Corporation of Canada has bought several
scientific findings from the Guangzhou Research Institute for
Utilization of Reclaimed Resources on scrap rubber recycling for
value added manufacturing and for devulcanizing agents at a
combined cost of 900,000 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
How to recycle used rubber tires in order to alleviate
pollution is a long-standing headache for western countries.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian company proclaimed that it will use the
techniques, which are of the world standard, to set up three
plants in the United States and Canada designed to turn scrap
rubber and motor vehicle tires into sound rubber products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
