<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Expressways to Be Built in North China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The provincial government of
Hebei is to increase the investment in building seven new
expressways by 1.4 billion yuan to bring the total amount to 4.6
billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
A big share of the investment, estimated at 400 million yuan,
will be used on a section in Hebei on the expressway between
Beijing and Shenyang. As a result, the section is expected to open
to traffic on July 1, 1999, three months ahead of schedule, said
provincial governor Ye Liansong.
</P>
<P>
Owing to increased government investment, the local sections on
the expressways between Baoding and Tianjin and between
Shijiazhuang and Huanghua with a total length of 120 km will start
operation by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Investment of Hebei in infrastructures as a whole will be
increased by 10 billion yuan this year in a bid to maintain a
sustained and rapid economic growth, Ye said.
</P>
<P>
Hebei ranks third in China in expressway construction with a
total length of 607 km already completed. It plans to complete
construction of nine new expressways in the upcoming two years to
bring the total traffic mileage to 1,400 km. 
</P>
</TEXT>
