<HEADLINE> Shanxi Adds Investment in Infrastructures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Shanxi province, a leading coal
producer in north China, is to increase the amount of investment
in infrastructures by 30 percent this year to reach 6.7 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Under a strategy of giving priority to coal, electricity, road
and waterwork development, the province is to complete the
construction of five expressways. The 94-km expressway between
Yuanping and the provincial capital of Taiyuan is expected to open
to traffic in early October, said Hu Fuguo, secretary of the
Provincial Committee of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
According to a long-term development plan, the provincial
government is to allocate 36.9 billion yuan to build roads in the
next five years, 15.9 billion yuan more than the previous five
years.
</P>
<P>
Operation of the new roads will create 748,000 job
opportunities and help generate 15 billion yuan in gross domestic
product.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, the length of new road in operation
totaled 12,489 km and that of expressways were 206 km.  
</P>
</TEXT>
