<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Officials Dismissed for Incompetence in Central Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- More than one hundred government
officials in China's Hunan Province have been dismissed or demoted
as a result of being found incompetent during an evaluation
process that began earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
In the city of Ruanjiang, as many as 39 were dismissed,
demoted, or even given disciplinary penalties for incompetence.
</P>
<P>
Five officials in the city of Yueyang managed to avoid being
sacked immediatedly but have been given a year of probation before
a final decision is made.
</P>
<P>
The old practice that Chinese officials could not be dismissed
as long as he or she did not commit major crimes has now been
abandoned in a growing number of places in China as it prepares to
open wider to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
A senior official with the Hunan government said that last year
the province worked out new regulations that specifically define
reasons for promotion, dismissal, or demotion of government
officials to try to systematize the selection procedure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Artificial Rain Project to Ease Yellow River Water Shortage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Qinghai Province in northwest China
where the Yellow River originates will carry out a three-year
artificial rain project to help ease water shortage in the
country's second longest river.
</P>
<P>
Starting this year, the province will use planes, rockets and
cannons to induce rain over the upper reaches of the Yellow River
during the six months from April to September. The operation
expects to bring 300 million to 600 million cubic meters of water
to the river.
</P>
<P>
The first act was carried out in mid April and the annual cost
is estimated at some three million yuan (about 375,000 US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Running through seven provinces in northwest and north China,
Yellow River is the main water source in the arid northern
areas. The deteriorating ecological environment in the upper
reaches of the river in the past dozen years has reduced the
already scarce rainfall in the region.
</P>
<P>
In longyangxia, the largest hydro-power station in the region,
the water level has fallen to a historical low. The station is
operating with difficulty.
</P>
<P>
Reduced rainfall has also caused flow stoppages in the middle
and lower reaches of the river. Last year alone, the lower reaches
suffered from 222 days of dry-ups. Last year, Qinghai Province
experimented several artificial rainfalls which added 280 million
cubic meters of water to the river. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Sinks 5 Rebel Boats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan navy eastern command
Thursday morning destroyed five Tamil rebel boats carrying
explosives to Mullaitivu from Vakarai on the eastern coast of the
country, informed sources here said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said at least 10 rebels were believed to have been
killed in this incident near Verugal in Trincomalee district on
the eastern coast of the island.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Voice of Tiger radio monitored in Vavuniya
Thursday announced that 13 of their cadres including four women
were killed by government troops during the past 24 hours in
northern Sri Lanka, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Military spokesman Sarath Munasinghe said at Thursday's press
conference that government troops and Tamil rebels fought pitched
battles on Wednesday in northern Sri Lanka and that 16 rebels were
killed while five soldiers also were killed.
</P>
<P>
About 12 soldiers were also injured when the Tamil rebels
attacked the army's defense lines at Paranthan town in the
northern Kilinochchi district, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-year war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
