<HEADLINE> Beijing to Build Electronic City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing plans to build an
Electronic City in its eastern suburbs which will cover 105,000
square kilometers in area.
</P>
<P>
The project is to be built on the capital's former electronic
center which was set up in 1952, the first electronic base built
after new China was founded in 1949.
</P>
<P>
According to a new development plan, the City will consist of
three parts: a residential area with a combined floor space of 1.2
million square meters, an industrial area and a trading center.
</P>
<P>
The trading center, covering 300,000 square meters, will boast
a group of joint ventures, super markets, exhibition center for
electronic products and an information network center.
</P>
<P>
The existing electronic center has a population of
200,000.  
</P>
