<HEADLINE> Hainan Approved to Conduct Small-scale Trade with Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China's island province of Hainan
has been granted by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation the right to do small-scale trade with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The effort aims to promote agricultural cooperation between
the two places, allowing Taiwan-funded enterprises to import
seedlings, chemical fertilizer, and pesticides, and to export some
mainland-made products to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan businesses have opened more than 200 agricultural
ventures in the province, involving some 100 million US
dollars. However, some of the joint ventures found it difficult to
purchase wanted production means.
</P>
<P>
Hainan is the seventh in the country to be entitled to do such
trade with Taiwan, after Fujian, Guangdong, Zhejiang, Jiangsu,
Shangdong provinces, and Shanghai Municipality. 
</P>
