<HEADLINE> Double-Track Project of Hangzhou-Zhuzhou Railway Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese railway workers have
completed double-tracking the railway between Hangzhou, capital in
east China's Zhejiang province, and Zhuzhou, an industrial city in
central-south China's Hunan province after 15 years' efforts.
</P>
<P>
The double track, equipped with automatic closing system,
boasts a total length of 911.1 km, of which 564 km runs through
Jiangxi Province, eat China. It cost 9.267 billion yuan (1.12
billion US dollars) of state investment.
</P>
<P>
The horizontal double track, one of China's major railway
arteries, will help alleviate railway transport strain in the
country, said experts. 
