<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Female Giraffe In China Has Record Number of Offsprings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- An Dan, a female giraffe in
Taiyuan, the capital of China's Shanxi Province, will give birth
to her seventh offspring this August, a record number, the city's
zoo reports.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old mother was born in Beijing and sent to Taiyuan
at the age of 4. One of the zoo keepers, Wang Jianming, says that
the life span of giraffes is 30 years on average, and their
childbearing age is generally below 20.
</P>
<P>
One giraffe in Wuhan, in Hubei Province, had five offsprings a
few years ago, which was the record until now, said Wang.
</P>
<P>
He says that two of An Dan's offsprings had found homes in
Wuhan and Chengdu, but that the rest had died at a young age.
</P>
<P>
The mother is reported to be in good condition and zoo keepers
believe that she could give birth after four months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
