<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Exhibits Cultural Relics of 7,000 Years Old </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Cultural relics of 7,000 years old
are part of the exhibits of an exhibition being held in north
China's port city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition consists of 150 photos and charts and 460 pieces
of cultural relics dating back 300 to 7,000 years, which are
unearthed in the Tianjin area.
</P>
<P>
These cultural relics include bronze wares, crystal wares and
gold and silver wares, as well as stone and porcelain articles,
and iron farming tools. All the relics are said to fully reflect
the development history of the Tianjin area from the New Stone Age
to the Ming (1368-1644) and Qing (1644-1911) dynasties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
