<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tobacco Prices Fall in Malawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Malawi tobacco auction floors
opened for this season's tobacco sales with lackluster interest
from the buyers and recorded low prices for the growers, Zambia
Daily Mail reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The average price for the tobacco sold so far averaged around
1.2 U.S. Dollars per kilograms, much lower than last year's
average price of 1.5 Dollars per kilograms.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, sales of tobacco in Malawi reached 158.1 million
kilograms, which represented an 11 percent drop in production.
</P>
<P>
The decrease in prices is attributed to the anti-smoking
campaign in the United States which is the major importer of
Malawi tobacco.
</P>
<P>
This has been worsened by the few tobacco buyers at the
auction floors in the country who, at times, collude to offer low
prices.
</P>
<P>
Tobacco exports, which account for about 62 percent of
Malawi's total exports, amounted to 5.5 billion Malawi Kwacha
(367 million Dollars) in 1997, a growth of 20.7 percent over
1996.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that this year's low tobacco prices could
adversely affect Malawi's economic performance which is largely
agriculture driven. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi to Rebouble Efforts Against Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, which has one tenth of China's population living under the
poverty line, has decided to basically eradicate poverty by the
end of next year.
</P>
<P>
This is a major decision of the regional government
recently. If the goal is realized, Guangxi will fulfill the
poverty relief plan of the central government one year ahead of
schedule.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, the central government worked out a plan asking for
efforts to solve the food and clothing problem of the country's 80
million rural population living below the poverty line in seven
years. By this year, Guangxi has eight million people without
enough food and clothing, most of them living in rocky mountain
areas.
</P>
<P>
According to Li Zhaochao, chairman of the regional government,
in the past five years, Guangxi has spent 3.8 billion yuan (457.8
million US dollars) in supporting diversified operations of poor
farmers.
</P>
<P>
Another over 400 million yuan were used for the resettlement of
some 150,000 poor farmers in 22 mountainous counties.
</P>
<P>
Through the efforts, people living under the poverty line were
reduced from eight to 3.66 million in 1997. Of the 49 poor
counties, 33 have been lifted above the poverty line.
</P>
<P>
The goal of this year is to help 1.1 million poor people get
rid of poverty, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts are also called for solving drinking water problems in
28 poor counties in the first half of this year, and lay roads to
every village next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
