<HEADLINE> Northwestern Chinese Autonomous Region Getting More Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region has become a popular investment spot as a result of
improved conditions and cooperation with eastern China and foreign
investors.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia got 800 million yuan from the cities of Shanghai and
Tianjin, and from Fujian, Jiangsu, Zhejiang, and Anhui provinces
to develop its resources. It also had at least 5,000
technology-cooperation projects.
</P>
<P>
It has an annual coal production capacity of 16 million tons,
and a generating capacity of 2 million kw. It is No.1 in Asia in
production of some non-ferrous metals.
</P>
<P>
A poverty-relief project is helping a million people in a
mountainous part of southern Ningxia. The village of Huaxi village
in Jiangsu Province has put two years into setting up a village
where 233 hectares of wasteland can be used and 6,000 peasants
moved, a project that has got 90 million yuan for ten enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Ningxia used over 60 million US dollars worth of
foreign investment, 41.9 percent more than for 1996 and approved
43 foreign-backed projects.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia has approved 512 foreign-backed projects, involving 560
million US dollars, in energy, transport and telecommunications,
agricultural by-products processing, and light industry. 
</P>
