<HEADLINE> New Yun-7 Aircraft Receive Air Worthiness Certificate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The China-made new Yun-7-200A
passenger plane has received the air worthiness certificate from
Chinese civil aviation authorities after two years of successful
trial fly.
</P>
<P>
This latest model of the Yun-7 family will be put on the
domestic and international market soon, civil aviation officials
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the officials, the Yun-7-200A made by an aircraft
manufacturer in Xi'an is safer, more economical, and easer to
maintain than conventional models.
</P>
<P>
The Yun-7-200A plane is said to be the first to be made
strictly in line with China's air worthiness regulations. It is
equipped with a Canadian-made engine, and a US-made propeller.
</P>
<P>
The Xi'an aircraft plant plans to start mass production of
Yun-7-200A soon. 
</P>
