engages in democratic change," it added.
</P>
<P>
In a speech in Connecticut Wednesday, Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright urged Suharto to take "an historic act of
statesmanship" to "preserve his legacy."
</P>
<P>
She was actually urging him to step down, officials here said.
