<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Province Developing Container Shipping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The international container business
has been developing rapidly in China's Fujian province, which will
have the largest container port in eastern China, at Xiamen's
Haicang Port.
</P>
<P>
Haicang is a joint-venture with a Hong Kong company, built at a
cost of 900 million yuan. It will have four 10,000-ton berths that
can handle a million tons annually. It will have service to Japan,
Europe, the United States, and South America. It now has a
500-meter wharf, a 400,000-sq.m. area, a 30,000-ton container
port, and a 20,000-ton bulk cargo port. It handled 158 ships
last year, with a total capacity of 260,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Fujian's container business has been growing by at least 30
percent annually, and last year, moved 730,000 TEUs, and this year
is expected to handle more than a million.
</P>
<P>
A port official says that they have handled 223,500 TEUs in the
first quarter of 1998, an increase of 33.7 percent from the same
period last year, and Xiamen and Fuzhou ports are now among
China's ten largest container ports. Other ports have also seen
rapid development.
</P>
<P>
To keep up with this development, Fujian has built more
highways and a special area for container shipping procedures at
the cities of Nanping, Sanming, and Longyan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Incomes on Rise for Residents of 12 Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A recent study has found that there
are 12 cities in China where a majority of the residents earn a
monthly income of more than 500 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Only 24 percent of the residents of Beijing, Shanghai,
Guangzhou, Chengdu, Shenyang, Tianjin, Xi'an, Jinan, Nanjing,
Wuhan, Kunming, and Fuzhou make less than 499 yuan, according to
the State Statistics Bureau study.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it found that 49 percent of these cities' residents
have incomes of from 500 to 999 yuan, and that 19 percent of these
cities' residents have income of from 1,000 to 1,499 yuan.
</P>
<P>
These cities, most of which are provincial capitals, have been
enjoying comparatively rapid economic growth, the study showed.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningxia Using Foreign Funds for Telecommunications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- North China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region has used 72 million US dollars worth of foreign
funds since 1992 to develop its post and telecommunications
sector.
</P>
<P>
A regional post and telecommunications bureau official says
that foreign funds accounted for 30 percent of the region's total
spending on posts and telecommunications for the past five years.
</P>
<P>
They were used for 423,000 program-controlled digital
telephones, 15,000 long-distance phone lines, and 16 microwave
transmission systems.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia also purchased 850 kilometers of optical fiber cables
for 18 cities and counties.
</P>
<P>
New equipment and technology has improved the region's post and
telecommunications industry, like a 66.5-million-U.S.-dollar
government loan from Belgium and Australia for 113,000
program-controlled telephone switching systems in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The official says that, during the 1996-2000 period, Ningxia
will use a 20-million-U.S.-dollar loan from the Japanese
government for 310,000 program-controlled phones and a
telecommunications system.
</P>
<P>
There are now 7.3 telephones for every 100 people in Ningxia,
more than the average in China. People in the capital of Yinchuan
can now phone directly to 195 countries and regions around the
world.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, the telephone coverage rate in Ningxia is expected to
be above 10 percent, and in Yinchuan, above 42 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Soeharto Resigns, Transfers Presidential post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
announced here Thursday morning his resignation after holding a
meeting with leadership members of the House of Representative
(DPR).
</P>
<P>
"In line with the article 8 of the 1945 Constitution, and after
deeply considering the opinion of the leaders of the House and
Chairmen of the DPR factions, I hereby decide to resign as the
President of Indonesia starting the moment I make this
announcement on Thursday 21st of May, 1998," Soeharto said.
</P>
<P>
In line with the 1945 Constitution, Vice President B.J. Habibie
will continue the remaining presidential term of office of
1998-2003, he added.
</P>
<P>
"For the support of the Indonesian people during my time
leading the nation, I express my gratitude and apology for any
mistakes and my shortcomings. May the Indonesia people, with
Pancasila (five principles for national construction) ideology and
the 1945 constitution, remain glorious," he added.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto, 76, who held the presidential post for the past 32
years, also said starting today, the Seventh Development Cabinet
is demissioned.
</P>
<P>
Because the situation does not allow for the presidential
oathtaking before the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), and to
avoid vacuum in the national leadership, "Vice President Habibie
right now will take oath before the Chairman of the Supreme Court
(MA)," Soeharto said.
</P>
<P>
Following the announcement of Soeharto, B.J. Habibie
immediately read out his oath as the country's third president.
</P>
<P>
"In the name of Allah, I swear, I will fulfill my obligation as
President of the Republic of Indonesia as best I can and as just
as possible, uphold the national constitution and adhere to all
laws and regulations honestly and serve the country and the
nation," said Habibie.
</P>
<P>
The article 8 of Indonesia's 1945 constitution states: "In the
event of the untimely demise or incapacity of the president, or
should he be unable to execute his duties during his term of
office, his office shall be assumed by the Vice President until
the expiry of that term."
</P>
<P>
Soeharto in his speech earlier said that he took the decision
to resign out of his understanding of the people's aspirations for
total reforms and for the sake of national unity.
</P>
<P>
He added that since his suggestion to set up a Reform Committee
did not receive favorable response from the public, so the planned
reshuffle of the Seventh Development Cabinet would no longer be
carried out.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto said that taking into account of the above-mentioned
matters, he decided to resign because it would be very difficult
for him to continue implementing the administration and
development.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, following the announcement, Defense and Security
Affairs Minister/Armed Forces Commander (ABRI) General Wiranto
declared the ABRI support to the resignation of Soeharto as well
as the appointment of B.J. Habibie as the new president.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto said: "After witnessing the transfer of presidential
post, the Minister of Defense and Security/Commander of the Armed
Forces will announce (the ABRI) political stance and make an
appeal to the whole people of Indonesia."
</P>
<P>
He said Firstly, understanding the development of the situation
and the people's aspirations, ABRI supports and welcomes the
resignation of Soeharto as President, and in line with the
Constitution, "we support Vice President B.J. Habibie as the new
president."
</P>
<P>
Secondly, ABRI, which remains solid and united, hopes and
appeals to the Indonesian people to accept the personal initiative
of President Soeharto, according to the article 8 of the 1945
Constitution.
</P>
<P>
Thirdly, in this case, ABRI will remain to play an active role
in preventing violations and other activities which threatens the
national unity.
</P>
<P>
Fourthly, to uphold national noble values, ABRI will protect
the safety and dignity of former President Soeharto and his
family.
</P>
<P>
Fifthly, ABRI calls on parties to remain calm in order to
prevent any violences and riots, which would eventually harm the
people themselves, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> DPRK to Hold Parliamentary Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Elections for the representatives
of the 10th Supreme People's Assembly (SPA) of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) will be held on July 26.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made Thursday by the Standing Committee of the
Ninth SPA in line with the DPRK constitution, local newspapers
reported.
</P>
<P>
According to Article 90 of the constitution, elections for the
new SPA should be held prior to the expiration of the incumbent
legislature under the decision of its Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The term of the present SPA would be prolonged in case
elections should be delayed due to unavoidable incidents, the
constitution stipulates.
</P>
<P>
687 representatives were elected to the current SPA on April
22, 1990.
</P>
<P>
The SPA, the top organ of state power in the DPRK, is
accredited with legislative power. Representatives are elected to
a five-year term.
</P>
<P>
The SPA Standing Committee is in charge of day-to-day business
when the assembly is not in session.
</P>
<P>
Yang Hyong Sop is chairman of the current Standing Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0249 </DOCNO>
