<HEADLINE> Share Prices Up on Singapore Market After Soeharto </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices shot up on the
Singapore market soon after Indonesian President Soeharto
announced his resignation Thursday morning, as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index increased sharply by 34.43 points
to end the morning session at 1308.21 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that share prices ended the morning session
higher, buoyed by euphoria following Soeharto's resignation.
</P>
<P>
But they were quick to add that the market eased from its
intra-day highs after learning that Vice President B.J. Habibie
was sworn in as new President of Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Habibie's appointment did little to quell concerns over the
introduction of much-needed reforms, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
