<DOCNO> XIE19980521.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Non-aligned Movement Seeks Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARTAGENA, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The coordinating bureau of the
Non-aligned Movement appealed to the developing countries
Wednesday to strengthen cooperation in international affairs to
achieve peace and social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
In a communique, the coordinating bureau said non-aligned
countries should make efforts to increase their influence and
roles in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
On economic globalization, it said the financial crisis in
southeast Asia, which started last July, showed that economic
globalization may bring negative results to developing countries.
</P>
<P>
It hoped industrialized nations would provide more help to
these Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
The coordinating bureau of the No-naligned Movement held a
ministerial meeting on Tuesday participated in by 104 ministers
and representatives.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, which ended Wednesday, Paraguay was admitted as
a new observer nation. The movement now has 113 member countries
and 13 observer nations. 
</P>
