<HEADLINE> Argentine Flood Victims Get IDB Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) is to grant Argentina a loan of more than 300 million
U.S. dollars to help flooded provinces.
</P>
<P>
Humberto Petrei, the Argentine representative at the IDB, said
half of the loan will be used in road construction, 100 million
dollars in agriculture and the rest of the funds in the social
sectors.
</P>
<P>
He added that the IDB will help form a guarantee fund for small
producers whose property cannot meet bank requirements for
securities. 
