<HEADLINE> Guerrilla Threat Halts Transport in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, May 20 (Xinhua)-- Transport on three main roads in the
north Nicaraguan province of Matagalpa has been paralyzed in fear of
guerrilla threats that vehicles will be attacked, a transport
organization said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A statement released by the MARUN transport cooperative said
it would suspend services from Tuesday to Saturday on routes
connecting Matagalpa to Rio Blaco, La Dalia, and Bocay-Wiwil
because of threats from the self-named Revolutionary Armed Front
(FAR).
</P>
<P>
The communique said a bus traveling to a place known as La
Tronca on Monday was intercepted and almost burned by armed men,
who asked the owner to provide them with 20 pairs of military
boots.
</P>
<P>
FAR, which is demanding the government release three of its
jailed members, has expressed total support to doctors who have
been on strike for three months seeking a significant wage
increase.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Matagalpa police chief Evenor Gutierrez said that
last week the army broke up a small group of five FAR members
close to San Ramon, in Matagalpa province, killing three FAR
members and confiscating some military equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
