<HEADLINE> Bosnia's Entities Agree to Revise History Textbooks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Bosnia's two political entities
have agreed to delete all content likely to arouse ethnic hatred
in their history textbooks, the Yugoslav news agency reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached between the Education Minister of the
Muslim-Croat Federation, Fahrudin Rizvanbegovic, and his Serbian
counterpart, Nenad Suzic, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Jacques Klein, deputy representative of Peace Implementation
Council of Bosnia, mediated in the talks.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, an expert team, comprising five education
officials from each of Bosnia's Serb, Croat and Muslim
communities, will delete all hatred-provoking or insulting content
in the textbooks before June 20.
</P>
<P>
Revised versions of the history textbooks of the two political
entities are to be published in Serbian, Croatian and Bosnian
languages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
