<HEADLINE> China Has Over 16 Million Mobile Phone Subscribers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The number of mobile phone
subscribers in China had exceeded 16.718 million by April,
according to latest statistics.
</P>
<P>
This placed China the world's third largest mobile phone power,
Chinese telecommunication authorities disclosed here today.
</P>
<P>
The number of mobile phone subscribers have grown at an annual
rate of 150 percent in recent years, making the sector a pillar of
the country's telecommunication industry.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that most of the cellular phone subscribers
registered this year are GSM digital phone users, bringing the
number of such users to 10.18 million by April. GSM phone was
introduced to China in the latter part of 1995, linking it with 27
other countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
At present, China's mobile phone telecommunication network
covers 31 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The authorities expect that the goal set to have 20 million
mobile phone subscribers by the year 2000 will be realized ahead
of schedule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
