<HEADLINE> U.S. Defense Secretary to Visit Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, May 20 (Xinhua) -- United States Defense
Secretary William Cohen will visit Brazil next week to discuss
military issues, the Brazilian press reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Cohen will arrive in Brasilia next Tuesday, where he will meet
Brazilian President Fernando Henrique Cardoso and high ranking
military officers. Talks will focus on the creation of a defense
ministry instead of the four military ministries existing in
Brazil, and the transfer of the command of the armed forces to a
civilian.
</P>
<P>
The Cardoso government hopes to set up the defense ministry
before the end of this year and the defense minister will be a
civilian.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is the only country in Latin America that has four
military ministries in the government. 
</P>
