<HEADLINE> Telecommunication Business Making Strides in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, the largest city in
southern China, had witnessed additional 47,000 telephone
subscribers in the first three months of this year, bringing the
total to 1.72 million.
</P>
<P>
This averages the city's urban telephone subscription to 54.4
telephones in per 100 persons, which is one of the highest in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the subscribers of cellular phone in Guangzhou have
reached 28,700, bringing the total users of such phone the city to
643,000.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Guangzhou now has 570,000 subscribers of beeper
pagers, and 12,000 Internet users.
</P>
<P>
To cater to the public need, the city has installed 20,000
public telephone stations with over 30,000 telephone lines. And
3,000 public telephones using IC card will be installed within
this year.  
