<HEADLINE> Hebei Expects Wheat Harvests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Wheat output of Hebei, a
leading wheat producer in north China, is to renew the historical
record this year if no adversities occur in the upcoming two weeks.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey from the satellite, the unit output of
wheat in Hebei will increase by three percent this year, while the
total wheat output is to be five percent higher than the pick year
of 13.4 billion kg set in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The province sown wheat on 2.7 million ha of land last year,
46,600 ha more than the previous year. Owing to plentiful rainfall
and higher temperature than normal years, the heading stage came
three to seven days ahead of schedule. Over 80 percent of the
wheat are of high quality.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 agro-technicians have been sent to prevent
plant disease and insect pests and guide field management.
</P>
