<HEADLINE> High-tech Zones in Liaoning Develop Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Province, a heavy
industrial center in northeast China, has built three state-level
and three provincial-level new and high-tech development zones,
which played a big role in promoting local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the provincial government approved the establishment
of 110 foreign-funded firms and construction of 17 projects with
each involving an investment of 20 million U.S. dollars in these
development zones, which cover a total area of 71.8 sq. km., said
Yang Derun, deputy head of the Provincial Science Commission.
</P>
<P>
These zones generated a combined business income of 57.77
billion yuan (6.97 billion US dollars) from industry and commerce
last year. Over 60 percent of the receipts came from the new and
high-tech sector.
</P>
<P>
State-listed development zones in the cities of Shenyang and
Dalian have forged ties with science parks in other countries.
</P>
<P>
This year, these development zones should give priority to
development of name-brand products, build more high-tech
enterprise groups and integrate industry more closely with
commerce, Yang said. 
</P>
