<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian's Property Rights Market Develops Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The property rights market of east
China's Fujian Province has developed steadily since it was
founded two years ago.
</P>
<P>
The property rights turnover of Fujian Provincial Property
Rights Trading Center has totaled more than 400 million yuan, (48
million US dollars) according to statistics of the center.
</P>
<P>
Over the last two years, the center has made continued efforts
to formulate rules and regulations and consolidate business.
</P>
<P>
The center has arranged for the purchase and merge of three
enterprises and participated in the transfer of the stock rights
of two listed companies. It has also appraised assets with a total
value of some 100 million yuan (12 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Currently, the center has property rights of 2.3 billion yuan
(277 million US dollars) and 87 million US dollars for changing
hands. The assets cover such sectors as agriculture, light
industry, chemicals, building materials, electronics, medicine and
real estate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
