<HEADLINE> China's Shandong Increases Investment Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province has
increased its investment overseas in recent years, official
figures show.
</P>
<P>
Shandong, one of China's economic powerhouses, has founded 646
enterprises in 66 countries and regions worldwide, with total
investment hitting 220 million US dollars, according to the
latest statistics of the provincial commission for foreign
economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Overseas Shandong-funded enterprises covers a dozen sectors
such as light industry, textile, machinery, electronics,
metallurgy and fishing and deal in foreign trade, processing,
marketing and industrial development.
</P>
<P>
A number of Shandong's large enterprises have reported good
business overseas. The Qingdao Hisense Group, for example, entered
South Africa in 1994 and its annual production capacity in the
African nation had exceeded 200,000 sets by 1996. During a Chinese
commodity fair in Sao Paul, Brazil in March, Hisense agreed to
cooperate with three local firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
