<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Madrid Takes Record Seventh Champions Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMSTERDAM, May 20 (Xinhua) -- A 66th-minute goal by Yugoslav
international Mijatovic lifted Real Madrid to another record, its
seventh win of the UEFA Chmapions Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish club ended Juventus' winning streak that started
two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Both sides played neatly with tight defense for most of the
match and Real Madrid did not find its scoring chance until its
Brazilian defender Roberto Carlos volleyed for a shot from within
the area.
</P>
<P>
Unguarded Mijatovic collected the loose rebounder from
Juventus goalkeeper Peruzzi and dribbled past the keeper to lob
the ball into the far corner of the goal for the winner.
</P>
<P>
Striker Filippo Inzaghi missed a couple of scoring chances for
the Italian side when his volleying shots went either slightly
over the crossbar or just on the wrong side of the post.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's triumph was indeed a sweet one for the Spanish
club that waited for a hiatus of 17 years to enter their first
final. It last lost the final 1-0 to Liverpool in 1981 and it
last won the cup in 1966.
</P>
<P>
Real Madrid, however, already held a record by winning the
Champions Cup the most times, in 1956, 1957, 1958, 1959, 1960 and
1966.
</P>
<P>
This was the eighth encounter between Real Madrid and
Juventus. The Spanish club now holds a win-lose record of 5-3.
</P>
<P>
Real Madrid downed Germany's Borussia Dortmund 2-0 on
aggregate to reach the Amsterdam final while Juventus defeated
French club Monaco 6-4 on aggregate for the final berth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
