<HEADLINE> South Africa Beat China in World Cup Hockey Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UTRECHT, Netherlands, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Pietie Coetzee scored
twice off two short corners to pace World Cup debutant South
Africa to a 2-1 win over three-time cuppers China at the 1998
World Cup Field Hockey Women's Tournament.
</P>
<P>
The South African forward got her goals at the sixth and 50th
minutes in the game whereas China pulled one back when Tang
Chunling deflected in a field goal in the dying seconds.
</P>
